SIMPLE: materially
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Materially
<hw>Ma*te"ri*al*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In the state
of matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do not mean that anything is separable from a body by fire that
was not <qex>materially</qex> preexistent in it.</q>
<rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In its essence; substantially.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An ill intention is certainly sufficient to spoil . . . an act in
itself <qex>materially</qex> good.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>In an important manner or degree; essentially;
<as>as, it <ex>materially</ex> concerns us to know the real motives of
our actions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Materialness</ent>⟦br⟧
